<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-Rp4UMCFRa-0/WGrO30XvnTI/AAAAAAAALYY/Sw9srwYgvM8E5SkWRFoiU7v6sSVd_CKPQCLcB/s1600/AIMG_7665.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="434" src="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-Rp4UMCFRa-0/WGrO30XvnTI/AAAAAAAALYY/Sw9srwYgvM8E5SkWRFoiU7v6sSVd_CKPQCLcB/s640/AIMG_7665.jpg" width="640" /></a></div><br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-XTYRYEE2lso/WGrO5bYvnmI/AAAAAAAALYc/8K57j6NpWEUNe7SvL_6AP9LR_Lqt6mBEwCLcB/s1600/AIMG_7747.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="410" src="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-XTYRYEE2lso/WGrO5bYvnmI/AAAAAAAALYc/8K57j6NpWEUNe7SvL_6AP9LR_Lqt6mBEwCLcB/s640/AIMG_7747.jpg" width="640" /></a></div>A bright couple of days to welcome in the New Year and an opportunity to make the most of the last day of the holidays. With much still to do before the return to school and work little <i>Pared y Cefn Hir</i> with its low but distinctive summit a mere 20 minutes walk from the car park at Cregennan Lakes was the perfect place for a half day's outing. Having sought out the best of the scrambling during the climb up to the summit the eastward continuation of the long low ridge that forms the hill gives several more short scrambling opportunities. Tomos and Martha hunted them out enthusiastically whilst taking good care to stay on the warm and sunny rock rather than straying into the shade where frost and streaks of ice remained all day. <br /><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://4.bp.blogspot.com/-MIh5VL39dIE/WGrO-Q66bCI/AAAAAAAALYk/n_tyyG5FdWU97jij3TKSJdspf2xe9dRFgCLcB/s1600/AP1020048.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="468" src=